# MVRP: Multiple Vehicle Routing Problem

## Overview
This repository contains an optimization model developed to route a vehicle fleet. The primary goal is to minimize travel costs and time while adhering strictly to capacity and distance constraints[cite: 1].

---

## Problem Statement
Unoptimized multi-vehicle routing causes uneven load distribution, delayed deliveries, and inflated fuel costs[cite: 1]. 

---

## Solution 
I built an automated model to dynamically assign and sequence delivery nodes[cite: 1]. This ensures that the model chooses the optimal path across the entire fleet[cite: 1].

---

## Methods
* Applied Mixed-Integer Programming (MIP) to compute optimal solutions[cite: 1].
* Utilized Python-based heuristics, specifically OR-Tools and Gurobi, for mathematical modeling[cite: 1].
* Designed a custom Reinforcement Learning (RL) environment[cite: 1].
* Integrated the RL environment with MIP heuristics to handle complex, large-scale constraints[cite: 1].

---

## Results
* The implemented model significantly reduced the overall travel distance[cite: 1]. 
* The project demonstrated a highly efficient and programmatic approach to dealing with dynamic routing problems in traffic engineering[cite: 1].

